modules.description: This module provides direct serialization and deserialization between MAC address values and S-expressions using the Sexplib0 format. It defines the type `t` as an alias for `Macaddr.t` and includes functions `sexp_of_t` and `t_of_sexp` for converting to and from S-expressions. It is used to enable S-expression-based data exchange for MAC addresses, particularly when integrating with systems like configuration files or network protocols that rely on this format.
